    markdown:
      "## create\n\n`client.authenticationProviders.create(name: string, settings: { idp_cert_fingerprint: string; idp_entity_id: string; idp_sso_target_url: string; idp_cert_fingerprint_algorithm?: 'sha1' | 'sha256' | 'sha384' | 'sha512'; }, short_name: string, active?: boolean, settings_url?: string): { data?: authentication_provider; }`\n\n**post** `/authentication_providers`\n\nCreates an authentication provider.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `name: string`\n  The name associated with the authentication provider.\n\n- `settings: { idp_cert_fingerprint: string; idp_entity_id: string; idp_sso_target_url: string; idp_cert_fingerprint_algorithm?: 'sha1' | 'sha256' | 'sha384' | 'sha512'; }`\n  The settings associated with the authentication provider.\n  - `idp_cert_fingerprint: string`\n    The certificate fingerprint for the identity provider (IdP)\n  - `idp_entity_id: string`\n    The Entity ID for the identity provider (IdP).\n  - `idp_sso_target_url: string`\n    The SSO target url for the identity provider (IdP).\n  - `idp_cert_fingerprint_algorithm?: 'sha1' | 'sha256' | 'sha384' | 'sha512'`\n    The algorithm used to generate the identity provider's (IdP) certificate fingerprint\n\n- `short_name: string`\n  The short name associated with the authentication provider. This must be unique and URL-friendly, as it's going to be part of the login URL.\n\n- `active?: boolean`\n  The active status of the authentication provider\n\n- `settings_url?: string`\n  The URL for the identity provider metadata file to populate the settings automatically. If the settings attribute is provided, that will be used instead.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ data?: { id?: string; activated_at?: string; active?: boolean; created_at?: string; name?: string; organization_id?: string; record_type?: string; settings?: object; short_name?: string; updated_at?: string; }; }`\n\n  - `data?: { id?: string; activated_at?: string; active?: boolean; created_at?: string; name?: string; organization_id?: string; record_type?: string; settings?: { assertion_consumer_service_url?: string; idp_attribute_names?: object; idp_cert_fingerprint?: string; idp_cert_fingerprint_algorithm?: 'sha1' | 'sha256' | 'sha384' | 'sha512'; idp_certificate?: string; idp_entity_id?: string; idp_slo_target_url?: string; idp_sso_target_url?: string; name_identifier_format?: string; provision_groups?: boolean; service_provider_entity_id?: string; service_provider_login_url?: string; }; short_name?: string; updated_at?: string; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst authenticationProvider = await client.authenticationProviders.create({\n  name: 'Okta',\n  settings: {\n  idp_cert_fingerprint: '13:38:C7:BB:C9:FF:4A:70:38:3A:E3:D9:5C:CD:DB:2E:50:1E:80:A7',\n  idp_entity_id: 'https://myorg.myidp.com/saml/metadata',\n  idp_sso_target_url: 'https://myorg.myidp.com/trust/saml2/http-post/sso',\n},\n  short_name: 'myorg',\n});\n\nconsole.log(authenticationProvider);\n```",
