    httpMethod: 'post',
    summary: 'Enqueue call',
    description: 'Put the call in a queue.',
    stainlessPath: '(resource) calls.actions > (method) enqueue',
    qualified: 'client.calls.actions.enqueue',
    params: [
      'call_control_id: string;',
      'queue_name: string;',
      'client_state?: string;',
      'command_id?: string;',
      'keep_after_hangup?: boolean;',
      'max_size?: number;',
      'max_wait_time_secs?: number;',
    ],
    response: '{ data?: { result?: string; }; }',
    markdown:
      "## enqueue\n\n`client.calls.actions.enqueue(call_control_id: string, queue_name: string, client_state?: string, command_id?: string, keep_after_hangup?: boolean, max_size?: number, max_wait_time_secs?: number): { data?: call_control_command_result; }`\n\n**post** `/calls/{call_control_id}/actions/enqueue`\n\nPut the call in a queue.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `call_control_id: string`\n\n- `queue_name: string`\n  The name of the queue the call should be put in. If a queue with a given name doesn't exist yet it will be created.\n\n- `client_state?: string`\n  Use this field to add state to every subsequent webhook. It must be a valid Base-64 encoded string.\n\n- `command_id?: string`\n  Use this field to avoid duplicate commands. Telnyx will ignore any command with the same `command_id` for the same `call_control_id`.\n\n- `keep_after_hangup?: boolean`\n  If set to true, the call will remain in the queue after hangup. In this case bridging to such call will fail with necessary information needed to re-establish the call.\n\n- `max_size?: number`\n  The maximum number of calls allowed in the queue at a given time. Can't be modified for an existing queue.\n\n- `max_wait_time_secs?: number`\n  The number of seconds after which the call will be removed from the queue.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ data?: { result?: string; }; }`\n\n  - `data?: { result?: string; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst response = await client.calls.actions.enqueue('call_control_id', { queue_name: 'support' });\n\nconsole.log(response);\n```",
