      "## refer\n\n`client.calls.actions.refer(call_control_id: string, sip_address: string, client_state?: string, command_id?: string, custom_headers?: { name: string; value: string; }[], sip_auth_password?: string, sip_auth_username?: string, sip_headers?: { name: 'User-to-User'; value: string; }[]): { data?: call_control_command_result; }`\n\n**post** `/calls/{call_control_id}/actions/refer`\n\nInitiate a SIP Refer on a Call Control call. You can initiate a SIP Refer at any point in the duration of a call.\n\n**Expected Webhooks:**\n\n- `call.refer.started`\n- `call.refer.completed`\n- `call.refer.failed`\n\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `call_control_id: string`\n\n- `sip_address: string`\n  The SIP URI to which the call will be referred to.\n\n- `client_state?: string`\n  Use this field to add state to every subsequent webhook. It must be a valid Base-64 encoded string.\n\n- `command_id?: string`\n  Use this field to avoid execution of duplicate commands. Telnyx will ignore subsequent commands with the same `command_id` as one that has already been executed.\n\n- `custom_headers?: { name: string; value: string; }[]`\n  Custom headers to be added to the SIP INVITE.\n\n- `sip_auth_password?: string`\n  SIP Authentication password used for SIP challenges.\n\n- `sip_auth_username?: string`\n  SIP Authentication username used for SIP challenges.\n\n- `sip_headers?: { name: 'User-to-User'; value: string; }[]`\n  SIP headers to be added to the request. Currently only User-to-User header is supported.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ data?: { result?: string; }; }`\n\n  - `data?: { result?: string; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst response = await client.calls.actions.refer('call_control_id', { sip_address: 'sip:username@sip.non-telnyx-address.com' });\n\nconsole.log(response);\n```",
