    markdown:
      "## send_sip_info\n\n`client.calls.actions.sendSipInfo(call_control_id: string, body: string, content_type: string, client_state?: string, command_id?: string): { data?: call_control_command_result; }`\n\n**post** `/calls/{call_control_id}/actions/send_sip_info`\n\nSends SIP info from this leg.\n\n**Expected Webhooks:**\n\n- `call.sip_info.received` (to be received on the target call leg)\n\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `call_control_id: string`\n\n- `body: string`\n  Content of the SIP INFO\n\n- `content_type: string`\n  Content type of the INFO body. Must be MIME type compliant. There is a 1,400 bytes limit\n\n- `client_state?: string`\n  Use this field to add state to every subsequent webhook. It must be a valid Base-64 encoded string.\n\n- `command_id?: string`\n  Use this field to avoid duplicate commands. Telnyx will ignore any command with the same `command_id` for the same `call_control_id`.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ data?: { result?: string; }; }`\n\n  - `data?: { result?: string; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst response = await client.calls.actions.sendSipInfo('call_control_id', { body: '{\"key\": \"value\", \"numValue\": 100}', content_type: 'application/json' });\n\nconsole.log(response);\n```",
