    response: '{ data?: { result?: string; }; }',
    markdown:
      "## update_client_state\n\n`client.calls.actions.updateClientState(call_control_id: string, client_state: string): { data?: call_control_command_result; }`\n\n**put** `/calls/{call_control_id}/actions/client_state_update`\n\nUpdates client state\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `call_control_id: string`\n\n- `client_state: string`\n  Use this field to add state to every subsequent webhook. It must be a valid Base-64 encoded string.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ data?: { result?: string; }; }`\n\n  - `data?: { result?: string; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst response = await client.calls.actions.updateClientState('call_control_id', { client_state: 'aGF2ZSBhIG5pY2UgZGF5ID1d' });\n\nconsole.log(response);\n```",
