    markdown:
      "## retrieve\n\n`client.conferences.retrieve(id: string, region?: 'Australia' | 'Europe' | 'Middle East' | 'US'): { data?: conference; }`\n\n**get** `/conferences/{id}`\n\nRetrieve an existing conference\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `id: string`\n\n- `region?: 'Australia' | 'Europe' | 'Middle East' | 'US'`\n  Region where the conference data is located\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ data?: { id: string; created_at: string; expires_at: string; name: string; record_type: 'conference'; connection_id?: string; end_reason?: 'all_left' | 'ended_via_api' | 'host_left' | 'time_exceeded'; ended_by?: object; region?: string; status?: 'init' | 'in_progress' | 'completed'; updated_at?: string; }; }`\n\n  - `data?: { id: string; created_at: string; expires_at: string; name: string; record_type: 'conference'; connection_id?: string; end_reason?: 'all_left' | 'ended_via_api' | 'host_left' | 'time_exceeded'; ended_by?: { call_control_id?: string; call_session_id?: string; }; region?: string; status?: 'init' | 'in_progress' | 'completed'; updated_at?: string; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst conference = await client.conferences.retrieve('id');\n\nconsole.log(conference);\n```",
