    markdown:
      "## send_dtmf\n\n`client.conferences.actions.sendDtmf(id: string, digits: string, call_control_ids?: string[], client_state?: string, duration_millis?: number): { data?: conference_command_result; }`\n\n**post** `/conferences/{id}/actions/send_dtmf`\n\nSend DTMF tones to one or more conference participants.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `id: string`\n\n- `digits: string`\n  DTMF digits to send. Valid characters: 0-9, A-D, *, #, w (0.5s pause), W (1s pause).\n\n- `call_control_ids?: string[]`\n  Array of participant call control IDs to send DTMF to. When empty, DTMF will be sent to all participants.\n\n- `client_state?: string`\n  Use this field to add state to every subsequent webhook. Must be a valid Base-64 encoded string.\n\n- `duration_millis?: number`\n  Duration of each DTMF digit in milliseconds.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ data?: { result: string; }; }`\n\n  - `data?: { result: string; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst response = await client.conferences.actions.sendDtmf('182bd5e5-6e1a-4fe4-a799-aa6d9a6ab26e', { digits: '1234#' });\n\nconsole.log(response);\n```",
