    markdown:
      "## list_active_calls\n\n`client.connections.listActiveCalls(connection_id: string, page[number]?: number, page[size]?: number): { call_control_id: string; call_duration: number; call_leg_id: string; call_session_id: string; client_state: string; record_type: 'call'; }`\n\n**get** `/connections/{connection_id}/active_calls`\n\nLists all active calls for given connection. Acceptable connections are either SIP connections with webhook_url or xml_request_url, call control or texml. Returned results are cursor paginated.\n\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `connection_id: string`\n\n- `page[number]?: number`\n\n- `page[size]?: number`\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ call_control_id: string; call_duration: number; call_leg_id: string; call_session_id: string; client_state: string; record_type: 'call'; }`\n\n  - `call_control_id: string`\n  - `call_duration: number`\n  - `call_leg_id: string`\n  - `call_session_id: string`\n  - `client_state: string`\n  - `record_type: 'call'`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\n// Automatically fetches more pages as needed.\nfor await (const connectionListActiveCallsResponse of client.connections.listActiveCalls('1293384261075731461')) {\n  console.log(connectionListActiveCallsResponse);\n}\n```",
