    markdown:
      "## list\n\n`client.customerServiceRecords.list(filter?: { created_at?: { gt?: string; lt?: string; }; phone_number?: { eq?: string; in?: string[]; }; status?: { eq?: 'pending' | 'completed' | 'failed'; in?: 'pending' | 'completed' | 'failed'[]; }; }, page[number]?: number, page[size]?: number, sort?: { value?: 'created_at' | '-created_at'; }): { id?: string; created_at?: string; error_message?: string; phone_number?: string; record_type?: string; result?: object; status?: 'pending' | 'completed' | 'failed'; updated_at?: string; webhook_url?: string; }`\n\n**get** `/customer_service_records`\n\nList customer service records.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `filter?: { created_at?: { gt?: string; lt?: string; }; phone_number?: { eq?: string; in?: string[]; }; status?: { eq?: 'pending' | 'completed' | 'failed'; in?: 'pending' | 'completed' | 'failed'[]; }; }`\n  Consolidated filter parameter (deepObject style). Originally: filter[phone_number][eq], filter[phone_number][in][], filter[status][eq], filter[status][in][], filter[created_at][lt], filter[created_at][gt]\n  - `created_at?: { gt?: string; lt?: string; }`\n  - `phone_number?: { eq?: string; in?: string[]; }`\n  - `status?: { eq?: 'pending' | 'completed' | 'failed'; in?: 'pending' | 'completed' | 'failed'[]; }`\n\n- `page[number]?: number`\n\n- `page[size]?: number`\n\n- `sort?: { value?: 'created_at' | '-created_at'; }`\n  Consolidated sort parameter (deepObject style). Originally: sort[value]\n  - `value?: 'created_at' | '-created_at'`\n    Specifies the sort order for results. If not given, results are sorted by created_at in descending order.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id?: string; created_at?: string; error_message?: string; phone_number?: string; record_type?: string; result?: { address?: { administrative_area?: string; full_address?: string; locality?: string; postal_code?: string; street_address?: string; }; admin?: { account_number?: string; authorized_person_name?: string; billing_phone_number?: string; name?: string; }; associated_phone_numbers?: string[]; carrier_name?: string; }; status?: 'pending' | 'completed' | 'failed'; updated_at?: string; webhook_url?: string; }`\n\n  - `id?: string`\n  - `created_at?: string`\n  - `error_message?: string`\n  - `phone_number?: string`\n  - `record_type?: string`\n  - `result?: { address?: { administrative_area?: string; full_address?: string; locality?: string; postal_code?: string; street_address?: string; }; admin?: { account_number?: string; authorized_person_name?: string; billing_phone_number?: string; name?: string; }; associated_phone_numbers?: string[]; carrier_name?: string; }`\n  - `status?: 'pending' | 'completed' | 'failed'`\n  - `updated_at?: string`\n  - `webhook_url?: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\n// Automatically fetches more pages as needed.\nfor await (const customerServiceRecord of client.customerServiceRecords.list()) {\n  console.log(customerServiceRecord);\n}\n```",
