    markdown:
      "## list\n\n`client.externalConnections.list(filter?: { id?: string; connection_name?: { contains?: string; }; created_at?: string; external_sip_connection?: 'zoom' | 'operator_connect'; phone_number?: { contains?: string; }; }, page[number]?: number, page[size]?: number): { id?: string; active?: boolean; created_at?: string; credential_active?: boolean; external_sip_connection?: 'zoom' | 'operator_connect'; inbound?: object; outbound?: object; record_type?: string; tags?: string[]; updated_at?: string; webhook_api_version?: '1' | '2'; webhook_event_failover_url?: string; webhook_event_url?: string; webhook_timeout_secs?: number; }`\n\n**get** `/external_connections`\n\nThis endpoint returns a list of your External Connections inside the 'data' attribute of the response. External Connections are used by Telnyx customers to seamless configure SIP trunking integrations with Telnyx Partners, through External Voice Integrations in Mission Control Portal.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `filter?: { id?: string; connection_name?: { contains?: string; }; created_at?: string; external_sip_connection?: 'zoom' | 'operator_connect'; phone_number?: { contains?: string; }; }`\n  Filter parameter for external connections (deepObject style). Supports filtering by connection_name, external_sip_connection, id, created_at, and phone_number.\n  - `id?: string`\n    If present, connections with <code>id</code> matching the given value will be returned.\n  - `connection_name?: { contains?: string; }`\n  - `created_at?: string`\n    If present, connections with <code>created_at</code> date matching the given YYYY-MM-DD date will be returned.\n  - `external_sip_connection?: 'zoom' | 'operator_connect'`\n    If present, connections with <code>external_sip_connection</code> matching the given value will be returned.\n  - `phone_number?: { contains?: string; }`\n    Phone number filter for connections. Note: Despite the 'contains' name, this requires a full E164 match per the original specification.\n\n- `page[number]?: number`\n\n- `page[size]?: number`\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id?: string; active?: boolean; created_at?: string; credential_active?: boolean; external_sip_connection?: 'zoom' | 'operator_connect'; inbound?: { channel_limit?: number; }; outbound?: { channel_limit?: number; outbound_voice_profile_id?: string; }; record_type?: string; tags?: string[]; updated_at?: string; webhook_api_version?: '1' | '2'; webhook_event_failover_url?: string; webhook_event_url?: string; webhook_timeout_secs?: number; }`\n\n  - `id?: string`\n  - `active?: boolean`\n  - `created_at?: string`\n  - `credential_active?: boolean`\n  - `external_sip_connection?: 'zoom' | 'operator_connect'`\n  - `inbound?: { channel_limit?: number; }`\n  - `outbound?: { channel_limit?: number; outbound_voice_profile_id?: string; }`\n  - `record_type?: string`\n  - `tags?: string[]`\n  - `updated_at?: string`\n  - `webhook_api_version?: '1' | '2'`\n  - `webhook_event_failover_url?: string`\n  - `webhook_event_url?: string`\n  - `webhook_timeout_secs?: number`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\n// Automatically fetches more pages as needed.\nfor await (const externalConnection of client.externalConnections.list()) {\n  console.log(externalConnection);\n}\n```",
