    httpMethod: 'get',
    summary: 'Lists accounts managed by the current user.',
    description:
      'Lists the accounts managed by the current user. Users need to be explictly approved by Telnyx in order to become manager accounts.',
    stainlessPath: '(resource) managed_accounts > (method) list',
    qualified: 'client.managedAccounts.list',
    params: [
      'filter?: { email?: { contains?: string; eq?: string; }; organization_name?: { contains?: string; eq?: string; }; };',
      'include_cancelled_accounts?: boolean;',
      'page[number]?: number;',
      'page[size]?: number;',
      "sort?: 'created_at' | 'email';",
    ],
    response:
      "{ id: string; api_user: string; created_at: string; email: string; manager_account_id: string; record_type: 'managed_account'; updated_at: string; managed_account_allow_custom_pricing?: boolean; organization_name?: string; rollup_billing?: boolean; }",
    markdown:
      "## list\n\n`client.managedAccounts.list(filter?: { email?: { contains?: string; eq?: string; }; organization_name?: { contains?: string; eq?: string; }; }, include_cancelled_accounts?: boolean, page[number]?: number, page[size]?: number, sort?: 'created_at' | 'email'): { id: string; api_user: string; created_at: string; email: string; manager_account_id: string; record_type: 'managed_account'; updated_at: string; managed_account_allow_custom_pricing?: boolean; organization_name?: string; rollup_billing?: boolean; }`\n\n**get** `/managed_accounts`\n\nLists the accounts managed by the current user. Users need to be explictly approved by Telnyx in order to become manager accounts.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `filter?: { email?: { contains?: string; eq?: string; }; organization_name?: { contains?: string; eq?: string; }; }`\n  Consolidated filter parameter (deepObject style). Originally: filter[email][contains], filter[email][eq], filter[organization_name][contains], filter[organization_name][eq]\n  - `email?: { contains?: string; eq?: string; }`\n  - `organization_name?: { contains?: string; eq?: string; }`\n\n- `include_cancelled_accounts?: boolean`\n  Specifies if cancelled accounts should be included in the results.\n\n- `page[number]?: number`\n\n- `page[size]?: number`\n\n- `sort?: 'created_at' | 'email'`\n  Specifies the sort order for results. By default sorting direction is ascending. To have the results sorted in descending order add the <code> -</code> prefix.<br/><br/>\nThat is: <ul>\n  <li>\n    <code>email</code>: sorts the result by the\n    <code>email</code> field in ascending order.\n  </li>\n\n  <li>\n    <code>-email</code>: sorts the result by the\n    <code>email</code> field in descending order.\n  </li>\n</ul> <br/> If not given, results are sorted by <code>created_at</code> in descending order.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id: string; api_user: string; created_at: string; email: string; manager_account_id: string; record_type: 'managed_account'; updated_at: string; managed_account_allow_custom_pricing?: boolean; organization_name?: string; rollup_billing?: boolean; }`\n\n  - `id: string`\n  - `api_user: string`\n  - `created_at: string`\n  - `email: string`\n  - `manager_account_id: string`\n  - `record_type: 'managed_account'`\n  - `updated_at: string`\n  - `managed_account_allow_custom_pricing?: boolean`\n  - `organization_name?: string`\n  - `rollup_billing?: boolean`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\n// Automatically fetches more pages as needed.\nfor await (const managedAccountListResponse of client.managedAccounts.list()) {\n  console.log(managedAccountListResponse);\n}\n```",
