    markdown:
      "## list\n\n`client.messagingHostedNumbers.list(filter[messaging_profile_id]?: string, filter[phone_number]?: string, filter[phone_number][contains]?: string, page[number]?: number, page[size]?: number, sort[phone_number]?: 'asc' | 'desc'): { id?: string; country_code?: string; created_at?: string; eligible_messaging_products?: string[]; features?: object; health?: number_health_metrics; messaging_product?: string; messaging_profile_id?: string; organization_id?: string; phone_number?: string; record_type?: 'messaging_phone_number' | 'messaging_settings'; tags?: string[]; traffic_type?: string; type?: 'long-code' | 'toll-free' | 'short-code' | 'longcode' | 'tollfree' | 'shortcode'; updated_at?: string; }`\n\n**get** `/messaging_hosted_numbers`\n\nList all hosted numbers associated with the authenticated user.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `filter[messaging_profile_id]?: string`\n  Filter by messaging profile ID.\n\n- `filter[phone_number]?: string`\n  Filter by exact phone number.\n\n- `filter[phone_number][contains]?: string`\n  Filter by phone number substring.\n\n- `page[number]?: number`\n\n- `page[size]?: number`\n\n- `sort[phone_number]?: 'asc' | 'desc'`\n  Sort by phone number.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id?: string; country_code?: string; created_at?: string; eligible_messaging_products?: string[]; features?: { mms?: object; sms?: object; }; health?: { inbound_outbound_ratio: number; message_count: number; spam_ratio: number; success_ratio: number; }; messaging_product?: string; messaging_profile_id?: string; organization_id?: string; phone_number?: string; record_type?: 'messaging_phone_number' | 'messaging_settings'; tags?: string[]; traffic_type?: string; type?: 'long-code' | 'toll-free' | 'short-code' | 'longcode' | 'tollfree' | 'shortcode'; updated_at?: string; }`\n\n  - `id?: string`\n  - `country_code?: string`\n  - `created_at?: string`\n  - `eligible_messaging_products?: string[]`\n  - `features?: { mms?: { domestic_two_way: boolean; international_inbound: boolean; international_outbound: boolean; }; sms?: { domestic_two_way: boolean; international_inbound: boolean; international_outbound: boolean; }; }`\n  - `health?: { inbound_outbound_ratio: number; message_count: number; spam_ratio: number; success_ratio: number; }`\n  - `messaging_product?: string`\n  - `messaging_profile_id?: string`\n  - `organization_id?: string`\n  - `phone_number?: string`\n  - `record_type?: 'messaging_phone_number' | 'messaging_settings'`\n  - `tags?: string[]`\n  - `traffic_type?: string`\n  - `type?: 'long-code' | 'toll-free' | 'short-code' | 'longcode' | 'tollfree' | 'shortcode'`\n  - `updated_at?: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\n// Automatically fetches more pages as needed.\nfor await (const phoneNumberWithMessagingSettings of client.messagingHostedNumbers.list()) {\n  console.log(phoneNumberWithMessagingSettings);\n}\n```",
