    response:
      '{ created_at?: string; from?: string; keyword?: string; messaging_profile_id?: string; to?: string; }',
    markdown:
      "## list\n\n`client.messagingOptouts.list(created_at?: { gte?: string; lte?: string; }, filter?: { from?: string; messaging_profile_id?: string; }, page[number]?: number, page[size]?: number, redaction_enabled?: string): { created_at?: string; from?: string; keyword?: string; messaging_profile_id?: string; to?: string; }`\n\n**get** `/messaging_optouts`\n\nRetrieve a list of opt-out blocks.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `created_at?: { gte?: string; lte?: string; }`\n  Consolidated created_at parameter (deepObject style). Originally: created_at[gte], created_at[lte]\n  - `gte?: string`\n    Filter opt-outs created after this date (ISO-8601 format)\n  - `lte?: string`\n    Filter opt-outs created before this date (ISO-8601 format)\n\n- `filter?: { from?: string; messaging_profile_id?: string; }`\n  Consolidated filter parameter (deepObject style). Originally: filter[messaging_profile_id], filter[from]\n  - `from?: string`\n    The sending address (+E.164 formatted phone number, alphanumeric sender ID, or short code) to retrieve opt-outs for\n  - `messaging_profile_id?: string`\n    The ID of the messaging profile to retrieve opt-outs for\n\n- `page[number]?: number`\n\n- `page[size]?: number`\n\n- `redaction_enabled?: string`\n  If receiving address (+E.164 formatted phone number) should be redacted\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ created_at?: string; from?: string; keyword?: string; messaging_profile_id?: string; to?: string; }`\n\n  - `created_at?: string`\n  - `from?: string`\n  - `keyword?: string`\n  - `messaging_profile_id?: string`\n  - `to?: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\n// Automatically fetches more pages as needed.\nfor await (const messagingOptoutListResponse of client.messagingOptouts.list()) {\n  console.log(messagingOptoutListResponse);\n}\n```",
