    markdown:
      "## list\n\n`client.otaUpdates.list(filter?: { sim_card_id?: string; status?: 'in-progress' | 'completed' | 'failed'; type?: 'sim_card_network_preferences'; }, page[number]?: number, page[size]?: number): { id?: string; created_at?: string; record_type?: string; sim_card_id?: string; status?: 'in-progress' | 'completed' | 'failed'; type?: 'sim_card_network_preferences'; updated_at?: string; }`\n\n**get** `/ota_updates`\n\nList OTA updates\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `filter?: { sim_card_id?: string; status?: 'in-progress' | 'completed' | 'failed'; type?: 'sim_card_network_preferences'; }`\n  Consolidated filter parameter for OTA updates (deepObject style). Originally: filter[status], filter[sim_card_id], filter[type]\n  - `sim_card_id?: string`\n    The SIM card identification UUID.\n  - `status?: 'in-progress' | 'completed' | 'failed'`\n    Filter by a specific status of the resource's lifecycle.\n  - `type?: 'sim_card_network_preferences'`\n    Filter by type.\n\n- `page[number]?: number`\n\n- `page[size]?: number`\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id?: string; created_at?: string; record_type?: string; sim_card_id?: string; status?: 'in-progress' | 'completed' | 'failed'; type?: 'sim_card_network_preferences'; updated_at?: string; }`\n  This object represents an Over the Air (OTA) update request. It allows tracking the current status of a operation that apply settings in a particular SIM card. <br/><br/>\n\n  - `id?: string`\n  - `created_at?: string`\n  - `record_type?: string`\n  - `sim_card_id?: string`\n  - `status?: 'in-progress' | 'completed' | 'failed'`\n  - `type?: 'sim_card_network_preferences'`\n  - `updated_at?: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\n// Automatically fetches more pages as needed.\nfor await (const otaUpdateListResponse of client.otaUpdates.list()) {\n  console.log(otaUpdateListResponse);\n}\n```",
