    markdown:
      "## create\n\n`client.rooms.create(enable_recording?: boolean, max_participants?: number, unique_name?: string, webhook_event_failover_url?: string, webhook_event_url?: string, webhook_timeout_secs?: number): { data?: room; }`\n\n**post** `/rooms`\n\nSynchronously create a Room.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `enable_recording?: boolean`\n  Enable or disable recording for that room.\n\n- `max_participants?: number`\n  The maximum amount of participants allowed in a room. If new participants try to join after that limit is reached, their request will be rejected.\n\n- `unique_name?: string`\n  The unique (within the Telnyx account scope) name of the room.\n\n- `webhook_event_failover_url?: string`\n  The failover URL where webhooks related to this room will be sent if sending to the primary URL fails. Must include a scheme, such as 'https'.\n\n- `webhook_event_url?: string`\n  The URL where webhooks related to this room will be sent. Must include a scheme, such as 'https'.\n\n- `webhook_timeout_secs?: number`\n  Specifies how many seconds to wait before timing out a webhook.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ data?: { id?: string; active_session_id?: string; created_at?: string; enable_recording?: boolean; max_participants?: number; record_type?: string; sessions?: room_session[]; unique_name?: string; updated_at?: string; webhook_event_failover_url?: string; webhook_event_url?: string; webhook_timeout_secs?: number; }; }`\n\n  - `data?: { id?: string; active_session_id?: string; created_at?: string; enable_recording?: boolean; max_participants?: number; record_type?: string; sessions?: { id?: string; active?: boolean; created_at?: string; ended_at?: string; participants?: room_participant[]; record_type?: string; room_id?: string; updated_at?: string; }[]; unique_name?: string; updated_at?: string; webhook_event_failover_url?: string; webhook_event_url?: string; webhook_timeout_secs?: number; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst room = await client.rooms.create();\n\nconsole.log(room);\n```",
