    name: 'update',
    endpoint: '/sim_cards/{id}',
    httpMethod: 'patch',
    summary: 'Update a SIM card',
    description: 'Updates SIM card data',
    stainlessPath: '(resource) sim_cards > (method) update',
    qualified: 'client.simCards.update',
    params: [
      'id: string;',
      'authorized_imeis?: string[];',
      "data_limit?: { amount?: string; unit?: 'MB' | 'GB'; };",
      'sim_card_group_id?: string;',
      'status?: { reason?: string; value?: string; };',
      'tags?: string[];',
    ],
    response:
      "{ data?: { id?: string; actions_in_progress?: boolean; authorized_imeis?: string[]; created_at?: string; current_billing_period_consumed_data?: object; current_device_location?: object; current_imei?: string; current_mcc?: string; current_mnc?: string; data_limit?: object; eid?: string; esim_installation_status?: 'released' | 'disabled'; iccid?: string; imsi?: string; ipv4?: string; ipv6?: string; live_data_session?: 'connected' | 'disconnected' | 'unknown'; msisdn?: string; pin_puk_codes?: object; record_type?: string; resources_with_in_progress_actions?: object[]; sim_card_group_id?: string; status?: sim_card_status; tags?: string[]; type?: 'physical' | 'esim'; updated_at?: string; version?: string; voice_enabled?: boolean; }; }",
    markdown:
      "## update\n\n`client.simCards.update(id: string, authorized_imeis?: string[], data_limit?: { amount?: string; unit?: 'MB' | 'GB'; }, sim_card_group_id?: string, status?: { reason?: string; value?: string; }, tags?: string[]): { data?: sim_card; }`\n\n**patch** `/sim_cards/{id}`\n\nUpdates SIM card data\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `id: string`\n\n- `authorized_imeis?: string[]`\n  List of IMEIs authorized to use a given SIM card.\n\n- `data_limit?: { amount?: string; unit?: 'MB' | 'GB'; }`\n  The SIM card individual data limit configuration.\n  - `amount?: string`\n  - `unit?: 'MB' | 'GB'`\n\n- `sim_card_group_id?: string`\n  The group SIMCardGroup identification. This attribute can be <code>null</code> when it's present in an associated resource.\n\n- `status?: { reason?: string; value?: string; }`\n  - `reason?: string`\n    It describes why the SIM card is in the current status.\n  - `value?: string`\n    The current status of the SIM card. It will be one of the following: <br/>\n<ul>\n <li><code>registering</code> - the card is being registered</li>\n <li><code>enabling</code> - the card is being enabled</li>\n <li><code>enabled</code> - the card is enabled and ready for use</li>\n <li><code>disabling</code> - the card is being disabled</li>\n <li><code>disabled</code> - the card has been disabled and cannot be used</li>\n <li><code>data_limit_exceeded</code> - the card has exceeded its data consumption limit</li>\n <li><code>setting_standby</code> - the process to set the card in stand by is in progress</li>\n <li><code>standby</code> - the card is in stand by</li>\n</ul>\nTransitioning between the enabled and disabled states may take a period of time.\n\n- `tags?: string[]`\n  Searchable tags associated with the SIM card\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ data?: { id?: string; actions_in_progress?: boolean; authorized_imeis?: string[]; created_at?: string; current_billing_period_consumed_data?: object; current_device_location?: object; current_imei?: string; current_mcc?: string; current_mnc?: string; data_limit?: object; eid?: string; esim_installation_status?: 'released' | 'disabled'; iccid?: string; imsi?: string; ipv4?: string; ipv6?: string; live_data_session?: 'connected' | 'disconnected' | 'unknown'; msisdn?: string; pin_puk_codes?: object; record_type?: string; resources_with_in_progress_actions?: object[]; sim_card_group_id?: string; status?: sim_card_status; tags?: string[]; type?: 'physical' | 'esim'; updated_at?: string; version?: string; voice_enabled?: boolean; }; }`\n\n  - `data?: { id?: string; actions_in_progress?: boolean; authorized_imeis?: string[]; created_at?: string; current_billing_period_consumed_data?: { amount?: string; unit?: string; }; current_device_location?: { accuracy?: number; accuracy_unit?: string; latitude?: string; longitude?: string; }; current_imei?: string; current_mcc?: string; current_mnc?: string; data_limit?: { amount?: string; unit?: 'MB' | 'GB'; }; eid?: string; esim_installation_status?: 'released' | 'disabled'; iccid?: string; imsi?: string; ipv4?: string; ipv6?: string; live_data_session?: 'connected' | 'disconnected' | 'unknown'; msisdn?: string; pin_puk_codes?: { pin1?: string; pin2?: string; puk1?: string; puk2?: string; }; record_type?: string; resources_with_in_progress_actions?: object[]; sim_card_group_id?: string; status?: { reason?: string; value?: string; }; tags?: string[]; type?: 'physical' | 'esim'; updated_at?: string; version?: string; voice_enabled?: boolean; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst simCard = await client.simCards.update('6a09cdc3-8948-47f0-aa62-74ac943d6c58');\n\nconsole.log(simCard);\n```",
