    markdown:
      "## list_wireless_connectivity_logs\n\n`client.simCards.listWirelessConnectivityLogs(id: string, page[number]?: number, page[size]?: number): { id?: number; apn?: string; cell_id?: string; created_at?: string; imei?: string; imsi?: string; ipv4?: string; ipv6?: string; last_seen?: string; log_type?: 'registration' | 'data'; mobile_country_code?: string; mobile_network_code?: string; radio_access_technology?: string; record_type?: string; sim_card_id?: string; start_time?: string; state?: string; stop_time?: string; }`\n\n**get** `/sim_cards/{id}/wireless_connectivity_logs`\n\nThis API allows listing a paginated collection of Wireless Connectivity Logs associated with a SIM Card, for troubleshooting purposes.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `id: string`\n\n- `page[number]?: number`\n  The page number to load.\n\n- `page[size]?: number`\n  The size of the page.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id?: number; apn?: string; cell_id?: string; created_at?: string; imei?: string; imsi?: string; ipv4?: string; ipv6?: string; last_seen?: string; log_type?: 'registration' | 'data'; mobile_country_code?: string; mobile_network_code?: string; radio_access_technology?: string; record_type?: string; sim_card_id?: string; start_time?: string; state?: string; stop_time?: string; }`\n  This object represents a wireless connectivity session log that happened through a SIM card. It aids in finding out potential problems when the SIM is not able to attach properly.\n\n  - `id?: number`\n  - `apn?: string`\n  - `cell_id?: string`\n  - `created_at?: string`\n  - `imei?: string`\n  - `imsi?: string`\n  - `ipv4?: string`\n  - `ipv6?: string`\n  - `last_seen?: string`\n  - `log_type?: 'registration' | 'data'`\n  - `mobile_country_code?: string`\n  - `mobile_network_code?: string`\n  - `radio_access_technology?: string`\n  - `record_type?: string`\n  - `sim_card_id?: string`\n  - `start_time?: string`\n  - `state?: string`\n  - `stop_time?: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\n// Automatically fetches more pages as needed.\nfor await (const simCardListWirelessConnectivityLogsResponse of client.simCards.listWirelessConnectivityLogs('6a09cdc3-8948-47f0-aa62-74ac943d6c58')) {\n  console.log(simCardListWirelessConnectivityLogsResponse);\n}\n```",
