    markdown:
      "## list\n\n`client.simCards.actions.list(filter?: { action_type?: string; bulk_sim_card_action_id?: string; sim_card_id?: string; status?: 'in-progress' | 'completed' | 'failed'; }, page[number]?: number, page[size]?: number): { id?: string; action_type?: 'enable' | 'enable_standby_sim_card' | 'disable' | 'set_standby'; created_at?: string; record_type?: string; settings?: object; sim_card_id?: string; status?: object; updated_at?: string; }`\n\n**get** `/sim_card_actions`\n\nThis API lists a paginated collection of SIM card actions. It enables exploring a collection of existing asynchronous operations using specific filters.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `filter?: { action_type?: string; bulk_sim_card_action_id?: string; sim_card_id?: string; status?: 'in-progress' | 'completed' | 'failed'; }`\n  Consolidated filter parameter for SIM card actions (deepObject style). Originally: filter[sim_card_id], filter[status], filter[bulk_sim_card_action_id], filter[action_type]\n  - `action_type?: string`\n    Filter by action type.\n  - `bulk_sim_card_action_id?: string`\n    Filter by a bulk SIM card action ID.\n  - `sim_card_id?: string`\n    A valid SIM card ID.\n  - `status?: 'in-progress' | 'completed' | 'failed'`\n    Filter by a specific status of the resource's lifecycle.\n\n- `page[number]?: number`\n\n- `page[size]?: number`\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id?: string; action_type?: 'enable' | 'enable_standby_sim_card' | 'disable' | 'set_standby'; created_at?: string; record_type?: string; settings?: object; sim_card_id?: string; status?: { reason?: string; value?: 'in-progress' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'interrupted'; }; updated_at?: string; }`\n  This object represents a SIM card action. It allows tracking the current status of an operation that impacts the SIM card.\n\n  - `id?: string`\n  - `action_type?: 'enable' | 'enable_standby_sim_card' | 'disable' | 'set_standby'`\n  - `created_at?: string`\n  - `record_type?: string`\n  - `settings?: object`\n  - `sim_card_id?: string`\n  - `status?: { reason?: string; value?: 'in-progress' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'interrupted'; }`\n  - `updated_at?: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\n// Automatically fetches more pages as needed.\nfor await (const simCardAction of client.simCards.actions.list()) {\n  console.log(simCardAction);\n}\n```",
