    markdown:
      "## create\n\n`client.storage.migrations.create(source_id: string, target_bucket_name: string, target_region: string, refresh?: boolean): { data?: migration_params; }`\n\n**post** `/storage/migrations`\n\nInitiate a migration of data from an external provider into Telnyx Cloud Storage. Currently, only S3 is supported.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `source_id: string`\n  ID of the Migration Source from which to migrate data.\n\n- `target_bucket_name: string`\n  Bucket name to migrate the data into. Will default to the same name as the `source_bucket_name`.\n\n- `target_region: string`\n  Telnyx Cloud Storage region to migrate the data to.\n\n- `refresh?: boolean`\n  If true, will continue to poll the source bucket to ensure new data is continually migrated over.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ data?: { source_id: string; target_bucket_name: string; target_region: string; id?: string; bytes_migrated?: number; bytes_to_migrate?: number; created_at?: string; eta?: string; last_copy?: string; refresh?: boolean; speed?: number; status?: 'pending' | 'checking' | 'migrating' | 'complete' | 'error' | 'stopped'; }; }`\n\n  - `data?: { source_id: string; target_bucket_name: string; target_region: string; id?: string; bytes_migrated?: number; bytes_to_migrate?: number; created_at?: string; eta?: string; last_copy?: string; refresh?: boolean; speed?: number; status?: 'pending' | 'checking' | 'migrating' | 'complete' | 'error' | 'stopped'; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst migration = await client.storage.migrations.create({\n  source_id: 'source_id',\n  target_bucket_name: 'target_bucket_name',\n  target_region: 'target_region',\n});\n\nconsole.log(migration);\n```",
