    markdown:
      "## update\n\n`client.texml.accounts.calls.update(account_sid: string, call_sid: string, FallbackMethod?: 'GET' | 'POST', FallbackUrl?: string, Method?: 'GET' | 'POST', Status?: string, StatusCallback?: string, StatusCallbackMethod?: 'GET' | 'POST', Texml?: string, Url?: string): { account_sid?: string; answered_by?: 'human' | 'machine' | 'not_sure'; caller_name?: string; date_created?: string; date_updated?: string; direction?: 'inbound' | 'outbound'; duration?: string; end_time?: string; from?: string; from_formatted?: string; price?: string; price_unit?: string; sid?: string; start_time?: string; status?: 'ringing' | 'in-progress' | 'canceled' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'busy' | 'no-answer'; to?: string; to_formatted?: string; uri?: string; }`\n\n**post** `/texml/Accounts/{account_sid}/Calls/{call_sid}`\n\nUpdate TeXML call. Please note that the keys present in the payload MUST BE formatted in CamelCase as specified in the example.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `account_sid: string`\n\n- `call_sid: string`\n\n- `FallbackMethod?: 'GET' | 'POST'`\n  HTTP request type used for `FallbackUrl`.\n\n- `FallbackUrl?: string`\n  A failover URL for which Telnyx will retrieve the TeXML call instructions if the Url is not responding.\n\n- `Method?: 'GET' | 'POST'`\n  HTTP request type used for `Url`.\n\n- `Status?: string`\n  The value to set the call status to. Setting the status to completed ends the call.\n\n- `StatusCallback?: string`\n  URL destination for Telnyx to send status callback events to for the call.\n\n- `StatusCallbackMethod?: 'GET' | 'POST'`\n  HTTP request type used for `StatusCallback`.\n\n- `Texml?: string`\n  TeXML to replace the current one with.\n\n- `Url?: string`\n  The URL where TeXML will make a request to retrieve a new set of TeXML instructions to continue the call flow.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ account_sid?: string; answered_by?: 'human' | 'machine' | 'not_sure'; caller_name?: string; date_created?: string; date_updated?: string; direction?: 'inbound' | 'outbound'; duration?: string; end_time?: string; from?: string; from_formatted?: string; price?: string; price_unit?: string; sid?: string; start_time?: string; status?: 'ringing' | 'in-progress' | 'canceled' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'busy' | 'no-answer'; to?: string; to_formatted?: string; uri?: string; }`\n\n  - `account_sid?: string`\n  - `answered_by?: 'human' | 'machine' | 'not_sure'`\n  - `caller_name?: string`\n  - `date_created?: string`\n  - `date_updated?: string`\n  - `direction?: 'inbound' | 'outbound'`\n  - `duration?: string`\n  - `end_time?: string`\n  - `from?: string`\n  - `from_formatted?: string`\n  - `price?: string`\n  - `price_unit?: string`\n  - `sid?: string`\n  - `start_time?: string`\n  - `status?: 'ringing' | 'in-progress' | 'canceled' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'busy' | 'no-answer'`\n  - `to?: string`\n  - `to_formatted?: string`\n  - `uri?: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst call = await client.texml.accounts.calls.update('call_sid', { account_sid: 'account_sid' });\n\nconsole.log(call);\n```",
