    response:
      "{ account_sid?: string; call_sid?: string; date_updated?: string; name?: string; sid?: string; status?: 'in-progress'; uri?: string; }",
    markdown:
      "## streams_json\n\n`client.texml.accounts.calls.streamsJson(account_sid: string, call_sid: string, BidirectionalCodec?: 'PCMU' | 'PCMA' | 'G722', BidirectionalMode?: 'mp3' | 'rtp', Name?: string, StatusCallback?: string, StatusCallbackMethod?: 'GET' | 'POST', Track?: 'inbound_track' | 'outbound_track' | 'both_tracks', Url?: string): { account_sid?: string; call_sid?: string; date_updated?: string; name?: string; sid?: string; status?: 'in-progress'; uri?: string; }`\n\n**post** `/texml/Accounts/{account_sid}/Calls/{call_sid}/Streams.json`\n\nStarts streaming media from a call to a specific WebSocket address.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `account_sid: string`\n\n- `call_sid: string`\n\n- `BidirectionalCodec?: 'PCMU' | 'PCMA' | 'G722'`\n  Indicates codec for bidirectional streaming RTP payloads. Used only with stream_bidirectional_mode=rtp. Case sensitive.\n\n- `BidirectionalMode?: 'mp3' | 'rtp'`\n  Configures method of bidirectional streaming (mp3, rtp).\n\n- `Name?: string`\n  The user specified name of Stream.\n\n- `StatusCallback?: string`\n  Url where status callbacks will be sent.\n\n- `StatusCallbackMethod?: 'GET' | 'POST'`\n  HTTP method used to send status callbacks.\n\n- `Track?: 'inbound_track' | 'outbound_track' | 'both_tracks'`\n  Tracks to be included in the stream\n\n- `Url?: string`\n  The destination WebSocket address where the stream is going to be delivered.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ account_sid?: string; call_sid?: string; date_updated?: string; name?: string; sid?: string; status?: 'in-progress'; uri?: string; }`\n\n  - `account_sid?: string`\n  - `call_sid?: string`\n  - `date_updated?: string`\n  - `name?: string`\n  - `sid?: string`\n  - `status?: 'in-progress'`\n  - `uri?: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst response = await client.texml.accounts.calls.streamsJson('call_sid', { account_sid: 'account_sid' });\n\nconsole.log(response);\n```",
