    markdown:
      "## recordings_json\n\n`client.texml.accounts.calls.recordingsJson.recordingsJson(account_sid: string, call_sid: string, PlayBeep?: boolean, RecordingChannels?: 'single' | 'dual', RecordingStatusCallback?: string, RecordingStatusCallbackEvent?: string, RecordingStatusCallbackMethod?: 'GET' | 'POST', RecordingTrack?: 'inbound' | 'outbound' | 'both', SendRecordingUrl?: boolean): { account_sid?: string; call_sid?: string; channels?: 1 | 2; conference_sid?: string; date_created?: string; date_updated?: string; duration?: string; error_code?: string; price?: string; price_unit?: string; sid?: string; source?: string; start_time?: string; track?: 'inbound' | 'outbound' | 'both'; uri?: string; }`\n\n**post** `/texml/Accounts/{account_sid}/Calls/{call_sid}/Recordings.json`\n\nStarts recording with specified parameters for call idientified by call_sid.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `account_sid: string`\n\n- `call_sid: string`\n\n- `PlayBeep?: boolean`\n  Whether to play a beep when recording is started.\n\n- `RecordingChannels?: 'single' | 'dual'`\n  When `dual`, final audio file has the first leg on channel A, and the rest on channel B. `single` mixes both tracks into a single channel.\n\n- `RecordingStatusCallback?: string`\n  Url where status callbacks will be sent.\n\n- `RecordingStatusCallbackEvent?: string`\n  The changes to the recording's state that should generate a call to `RecoridngStatusCallback`. Can be: `in-progress`, `completed` and `absent`. Separate multiple values with a space. Defaults to `completed`.\n\n- `RecordingStatusCallbackMethod?: 'GET' | 'POST'`\n  HTTP method used to send status callbacks.\n\n- `RecordingTrack?: 'inbound' | 'outbound' | 'both'`\n  The audio track to record for the call. The default is `both`.\n\n- `SendRecordingUrl?: boolean`\n  Whether to send RecordingUrl in webhooks.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ account_sid?: string; call_sid?: string; channels?: 1 | 2; conference_sid?: string; date_created?: string; date_updated?: string; duration?: string; error_code?: string; price?: string; price_unit?: string; sid?: string; source?: string; start_time?: string; track?: 'inbound' | 'outbound' | 'both'; uri?: string; }`\n\n  - `account_sid?: string`\n  - `call_sid?: string`\n  - `channels?: 1 | 2`\n  - `conference_sid?: string`\n  - `date_created?: string`\n  - `date_updated?: string`\n  - `duration?: string`\n  - `error_code?: string`\n  - `price?: string`\n  - `price_unit?: string`\n  - `sid?: string`\n  - `source?: string`\n  - `start_time?: string`\n  - `track?: 'inbound' | 'outbound' | 'both'`\n  - `uri?: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst response = await client.texml.accounts.calls.recordingsJson.recordingsJson('call_sid', { account_sid: 'account_sid' });\n\nconsole.log(response);\n```",
