    markdown:
      '## update\n\n`client.verifyProfiles.update(verify_profile_id: string, call?: { app_name?: string; code_length?: number; default_verification_timeout_secs?: number; messaging_template_id?: string; whitelisted_destinations?: string[]; }, flashcall?: { app_name?: string; default_verification_timeout_secs?: number; whitelisted_destinations?: string[]; }, language?: string, name?: string, rcs?: { app_name?: string; code_length?: number; default_verification_timeout_secs?: number; messaging_template_id?: string; sms_fallback?: boolean; whitelisted_destinations?: string[]; }, sms?: { alpha_sender?: string; app_name?: string; code_length?: number; default_verification_timeout_secs?: number; messaging_template_id?: string; whitelisted_destinations?: string[]; }, webhook_failover_url?: string, webhook_url?: string, whatsapp?: { app_name?: string; default_verification_timeout_secs?: number; whitelisted_destinations?: string[]; }): { data?: verify_profile; }`\n\n**patch** `/verify_profiles/{verify_profile_id}`\n\nUpdate Verify profile\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `verify_profile_id: string`\n\n- `call?: { app_name?: string; code_length?: number; default_verification_timeout_secs?: number; messaging_template_id?: string; whitelisted_destinations?: string[]; }`\n  - `app_name?: string`\n    The name that identifies the application requesting 2fa in the verification message.\n  - `code_length?: number`\n    The length of the verify code to generate.\n  - `default_verification_timeout_secs?: number`\n    For every request that is initiated via this Verify profile, this sets the number of seconds before a verification request code expires. Once the verification request expires, the user cannot use the code to verify their identity.\n  - `messaging_template_id?: string`\n    The message template identifier selected from /verify_profiles/templates\n  - `whitelisted_destinations?: string[]`\n    Enabled country destinations to send verification codes. The elements in the list must be valid ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country codes. If set to `["*"]`, all destinations will be allowed.\n\n- `flashcall?: { app_name?: string; default_verification_timeout_secs?: number; whitelisted_destinations?: string[]; }`\n  - `app_name?: string`\n    The name that identifies the application requesting 2fa in the verification message.\n  - `default_verification_timeout_secs?: number`\n    For every request that is initiated via this Verify profile, this sets the number of seconds before a verification request code expires. Once the verification request expires, the user cannot use the code to verify their identity.\n  - `whitelisted_destinations?: string[]`\n    Enabled country destinations to send verification codes. The elements in the list must be valid ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country codes. If set to `["*"]`, all destinations will be allowed.\n\n- `language?: string`\n\n- `name?: string`\n\n- `rcs?: { app_name?: string; code_length?: number; default_verification_timeout_secs?: number; messaging_template_id?: string; sms_fallback?: boolean; whitelisted_destinations?: string[]; }`\n  - `app_name?: string`\n    The name that identifies the application requesting 2fa in the verification message.\n  - `code_length?: number`\n    The length of the verify code to generate.\n  - `default_verification_timeout_secs?: number`\n    For every request that is initiated via this Verify profile, this sets the number of seconds before a verification request code expires. Once the verification request expires, the user cannot use the code to verify their identity.\n  - `messaging_template_id?: string`\n    The message template identifier selected from /verify_profiles/templates\n  - `sms_fallback?: boolean`\n    Enable SMS fallback when RCS delivery fails.\n  - `whitelisted_destinations?: string[]`\n    Enabled country destinations to send verification codes. The elements in the list must be valid ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country codes. If set to `["*"]`, all destinations will be allowed.\n\n- `sms?: { alpha_sender?: string; app_name?: string; code_length?: number; default_verification_timeout_secs?: number; messaging_template_id?: string; whitelisted_destinations?: string[]; }`\n  - `alpha_sender?: string`\n    The alphanumeric sender ID to use when sending to destinations that require an alphanumeric sender ID.\n  - `app_name?: string`\n    The name that identifies the application requesting 2fa in the verification message.\n  - `code_length?: number`\n    The length of the verify code to generate.\n  - `default_verification_timeout_secs?: number`\n    For every request that is initiated via this Verify profile, this sets the number of seconds before a verification request code expires. Once the verification request expires, the user cannot use the code to verify their identity.\n  - `messaging_template_id?: string`\n    The message template identifier selected from /verify_profiles/templates\n  - `whitelisted_destinations?: string[]`\n    Enabled country destinations to send verification codes. The elements in the list must be valid ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country codes. If set to `["*"]`, all destinations will be allowed.\n\n- `webhook_failover_url?: string`\n\n- `webhook_url?: string`\n\n- `whatsapp?: { app_name?: string; default_verification_timeout_secs?: number; whitelisted_destinations?: string[]; }`\n  - `app_name?: string`\n    The name that identifies the application requesting 2fa in the verification message.\n  - `default_verification_timeout_secs?: number`\n    For every request that is initiated via this Verify profile, this sets the number of seconds before a verification request code expires. Once the verification request expires, the user cannot use the code to verify their identity.\n  - `whitelisted_destinations?: string[]`\n    Enabled country destinations to send verification codes. The elements in the list must be valid ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country codes. If set to `["*"]`, all destinations will be allowed.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ data?: { id?: string; call?: object; created_at?: string; flashcall?: object; language?: string; name?: string; rcs?: object; record_type?: \'verification_profile\'; sms?: object; updated_at?: string; webhook_failover_url?: string; webhook_url?: string; }; }`\n\n  - `data?: { id?: string; call?: { app_name?: string; code_length?: number; default_verification_timeout_secs?: number; messaging_template_id?: string; whitelisted_destinations?: string[]; }; created_at?: string; flashcall?: { app_name?: string; default_verification_timeout_secs?: number; }; language?: string; name?: string; rcs?: { app_name?: string; code_length?: number; default_verification_timeout_secs?: number; messaging_template_id?: string; sms_fallback?: boolean; whitelisted_destinations?: string[]; }; record_type?: \'verification_profile\'; sms?: { alpha_sender?: string; app_name?: string; code_length?: number; default_verification_timeout_secs?: number; messaging_template_id?: string; whitelisted_destinations?: string[]; }; updated_at?: string; webhook_failover_url?: string; webhook_url?: string; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from \'telnyx\';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst verifyProfileData = await client.verifyProfiles.update(\'12ade33a-21c0-473b-b055-b3c836e1c292\');\n\nconsole.log(verifyProfileData);\n```',
