    markdown:
      "## revet\n\n`client.messaging10dlc.brand.revet(brandId: string): { brandRelationship: 'BASIC_ACCOUNT' | 'SMALL_ACCOUNT' | 'MEDIUM_ACCOUNT' | 'LARGE_ACCOUNT' | 'KEY_ACCOUNT'; country: string; displayName: string; email: string; entityType: entity_type; vertical: string; altBusinessId?: string; altBusinessIdType?: alt_business_id_type; brandId?: string; businessContactEmail?: string; city?: string; companyName?: string; createdAt?: string; cspId?: string; ein?: string; failureReasons?: string; firstName?: string; identityStatus?: brand_identity_status; ipAddress?: string; isReseller?: boolean; lastName?: string; mobilePhone?: string; mock?: boolean; optionalAttributes?: brand_optional_attributes; phone?: string; postalCode?: string; referenceId?: string; state?: string; status?: 'OK' | 'REGISTRATION_PENDING' | 'REGISTRATION_FAILED'; stockExchange?: stock_exchange; stockSymbol?: string; street?: string; tcrBrandId?: string; universalEin?: string; updatedAt?: string; webhookFailoverURL?: string; webhookURL?: string; website?: string; }`\n\n**put** `/10dlc/brand/{brandId}/revet`\n\nThis operation allows you to revet the brand. However, revetting is allowed once after the successful brand registration and thereafter limited to once every 3 months.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `brandId: string`\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ brandRelationship: 'BASIC_ACCOUNT' | 'SMALL_ACCOUNT' | 'MEDIUM_ACCOUNT' | 'LARGE_ACCOUNT' | 'KEY_ACCOUNT'; country: string; displayName: string; email: string; entityType: 'PRIVATE_PROFIT' | 'PUBLIC_PROFIT' | 'NON_PROFIT' | 'GOVERNMENT' | 'SOLE_PROPRIETOR'; vertical: string; altBusinessId?: string; altBusinessIdType?: 'NONE' | 'DUNS' | 'GIIN' | 'LEI'; brandId?: string; businessContactEmail?: string; city?: string; companyName?: string; createdAt?: string; cspId?: string; ein?: string; failureReasons?: string; firstName?: string; identityStatus?: 'VERIFIED' | 'UNVERIFIED' | 'SELF_DECLARED' | 'VETTED_VERIFIED'; ipAddress?: string; isReseller?: boolean; lastName?: string; mobilePhone?: string; mock?: boolean; optionalAttributes?: { taxExemptStatus?: string; }; phone?: string; postalCode?: string; referenceId?: string; state?: string; status?: 'OK' | 'REGISTRATION_PENDING' | 'REGISTRATION_FAILED'; stockExchange?: string; stockSymbol?: string; street?: string; tcrBrandId?: string; universalEin?: string; updatedAt?: string; webhookFailoverURL?: string; webhookURL?: string; website?: string; }`\n  Telnyx-specific extensions to The Campaign Registry's `Brand` type\n\n  - `brandRelationship: 'BASIC_ACCOUNT' | 'SMALL_ACCOUNT' | 'MEDIUM_ACCOUNT' | 'LARGE_ACCOUNT' | 'KEY_ACCOUNT'`\n  - `country: string`\n  - `displayName: string`\n  - `email: string`\n  - `entityType: 'PRIVATE_PROFIT' | 'PUBLIC_PROFIT' | 'NON_PROFIT' | 'GOVERNMENT' | 'SOLE_PROPRIETOR'`\n  - `vertical: string`\n  - `altBusinessId?: string`\n  - `altBusinessIdType?: 'NONE' | 'DUNS' | 'GIIN' | 'LEI'`\n  - `brandId?: string`\n  - `businessContactEmail?: string`\n  - `city?: string`\n  - `companyName?: string`\n  - `createdAt?: string`\n  - `cspId?: string`\n  - `ein?: string`\n  - `failureReasons?: string`\n  - `firstName?: string`\n  - `identityStatus?: 'VERIFIED' | 'UNVERIFIED' | 'SELF_DECLARED' | 'VETTED_VERIFIED'`\n  - `ipAddress?: string`\n  - `isReseller?: boolean`\n  - `lastName?: string`\n  - `mobilePhone?: string`\n  - `mock?: boolean`\n  - `optionalAttributes?: { taxExemptStatus?: string; }`\n  - `phone?: string`\n  - `postalCode?: string`\n  - `referenceId?: string`\n  - `state?: string`\n  - `status?: 'OK' | 'REGISTRATION_PENDING' | 'REGISTRATION_FAILED'`\n  - `stockExchange?: string`\n  - `stockSymbol?: string`\n  - `street?: string`\n  - `tcrBrandId?: string`\n  - `universalEin?: string`\n  - `updatedAt?: string`\n  - `webhookFailoverURL?: string`\n  - `webhookURL?: string`\n  - `website?: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst telnyxBrand = await client.messaging10dlc.brand.revet('brandId');\n\nconsole.log(telnyxBrand);\n```",
