      "## retrieve\n\n`client.sessionAnalysis.retrieve(record_type: string, event_id: string, date_time?: string, expand?: 'record' | 'none', include_children?: boolean, max_depth?: number): { cost: object; created_at: string; meta: object; root: event_node; session_id: string; status: string; completed_at?: string; }`\n\n**get** `/session_analysis/{record_type}/{event_id}`\n\nRetrieves a full session analysis tree for a given event, including costs, child events, and product linkages.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `record_type: string`\n\n- `event_id: string`\n\n- `date_time?: string`\n  ISO 8601 timestamp to narrow index selection for faster lookups.\n\n- `expand?: 'record' | 'none'`\n  Controls what data to expand on each event node.\n\n- `include_children?: boolean`\n  Whether to include child events in the response.\n\n- `max_depth?: number`\n  Maximum traversal depth for the event tree.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ cost: { currency: string; total: string; }; created_at: string; meta: { event_count: number; products: string[]; }; root: { id: string; children: event_node[]; cost: object; event_name: string; links: object; product: string; record: object; relationship?: object; }; session_id: string; status: string; completed_at?: string; }`\n\n  - `cost: { currency: string; total: string; }`\n  - `created_at: string`\n  - `meta: { event_count: number; products: string[]; }`\n  - `root: { id: string; children: { id: string; children: event_node[]; cost: object; event_name: string; links: object; product: string; record: object; relationship?: object; }[]; cost: { cumulative_cost: string; currency: string; event_cost: string; }; event_name: string; links: { records: string; self: string; }; product: string; record: object; relationship?: { parent_id: string; type: string; via: { local_field: string; parent_field: string; }; }; }`\n  - `session_id: string`\n  - `status: string`\n  - `completed_at?: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst sessionAnalysis = await client.sessionAnalysis.retrieve('182bd5e5-6e1a-4fe4-a799-aa6d9a6ab26e', { record_type: 'record_type' });\n\nconsole.log(sessionAnalysis);\n```",
