    markdown:
      "## update\n\n`client.voiceClones.update(id: string, name: string, gender?: 'male' | 'female' | 'neutral', language?: string): { data?: voice_clone_data; }`\n\n**patch** `/voice_clones/{id}`\n\nUpdates the name, language, or gender of a voice clone.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `id: string`\n\n- `name: string`\n  New name for the voice clone.\n\n- `gender?: 'male' | 'female' | 'neutral'`\n  Updated gender for the voice clone.\n\n- `language?: string`\n  Updated ISO 639-1 language code or `auto`.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ data?: { id?: string; created_at?: string; gender?: 'male' | 'female' | 'neutral'; label?: string; language?: string; name?: string; provider?: 'telnyx' | 'minimax'; provider_supported_models?: string[]; provider_voice_id?: string; record_type?: 'voice_clone'; source_voice_design_id?: string; source_voice_design_version?: number; updated_at?: string; }; }`\n  Response envelope for a single voice clone.\n\n  - `data?: { id?: string; created_at?: string; gender?: 'male' | 'female' | 'neutral'; label?: string; language?: string; name?: string; provider?: 'telnyx' | 'minimax'; provider_supported_models?: string[]; provider_voice_id?: string; record_type?: 'voice_clone'; source_voice_design_id?: string; source_voice_design_version?: number; updated_at?: string; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Telnyx from 'telnyx';\n\nconst client = new Telnyx();\n\nconst voiceClone = await client.voiceClones.update('182bd5e5-6e1a-4fe4-a799-aa6d9a6ab26e', { name: 'updated-clone' });\n\nconsole.log(voiceClone);\n```",
